  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Diocesan Coordination for Development Projects--Fundacion Trinity 2015 Iglesia Episcopal en Colombia Bogota Diocesan Office</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Colombia has approximately 3 million internally displaced people, the second largest internal refugee problem in the world after Darfur, caused by violence from the civil war. Some sources have indicated that in the Choco region, for example, there is one doctor per 10,000 people, but one soldier per 180 people. Also, the unemployment rate is 85% and the average person makes only US$250 per year; or less than US$1 per day. Colombian society is one of the most unequal in terms of economic wealth in the world. As a result, there is wide social and economic exclusion and huge rich to poor disparities. In the city of Cali, chronic poverty caused by social and economic exclusion and violence, has caused child malnutrition, high incidences of HIV-AIDS, family disintegration, intra-familial violence, and lack of income earning opportunities especially for women. In Quibdo, the capital of Choco, unemployed youth and street children are affected by crushing poverty, violence, and lack of economic opportunities. Great social inequality and marginalized populations of youth are easy victims of violence, prostitution, and being forced into serving with illegal armed groups. As a result, Episcopal Relief &amp;amp; Development has implemented a pilot project in partnership with the the Diocese in Colombia, to implement a microcredit project in Cali targeting women, and a youth education and training project in Quibdo, Choco. In addition, the partnership will strengthen the church&apos;s capacity to guide and expand this program to other regions for increased impact.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Identify, evaluate and approve up to 80 loans for individuals.,Identify, evaluate and approve loans for productive savings groups.,Disbursement of microcredit.,Train up to 130 people in financial and business management.,Develop a microcredit methodology that outlines target clients, requirements and procedures ,Form and train 32 new savings groups.,Identification of 4 replicators in Guambia,Refresher training for Faciliators.,Support and Monitor 34 continuing groups.,Conduct trainings in financial and business management for 30-60 savings groups.</narrative>
  </description>
